hi tres … Christo Iesu</char>) vg<char style="add">mss</char> (Cyprian) (Ps-Cyprian) (Priscillian) Speculum Varimadum Ps-Vigilius Fulgentius</char></note>, καὶ οἱ τρεῖς εἰς τὸ ἕν εἰσιν. <verse number="9" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.9 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">τὴν … ἀνθρώπων </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 5:32-34">Jn 5.32‑34</ref> </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ἡ … θεοῦ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 5:37">Jn 5.37</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 8:18">8.18</ref></char></note>εἰ τὴν μαρτυρίαν τῶν ἀνθρώπων λαμβάνομεν, ἡ μαρτυρία τοῦ θεοῦ μείζων ἐστίν· ὅτι αὕτη ἐστὶν ἡ μαρτυρία τοῦ θεοῦ, ὅτι μεμαρτύρηκεν περὶ τοῦ υἱοῦ αὐτοῦ. <verse number="10" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.10 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ πιστεύων … αὐτῷ </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="ROM 8:16">Ro 8.16</ref>; <ref loc="GAL 4:6">Ga 4.6</ref></char></note>ὁ πιστεύων εἰς τὸν υἱὸν τοῦ θεοῦ ἔχει τὴν μαρτυρίαν ἐν αὐτῷ<note caller="5" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν αὐτῷ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">B<char style="add">2</char> 307 436 442 642 1175 1448 1735 1852 1881* 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char><char style="add">pt</char> [K L] <char style="it">Lect</char> slav ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐν ἑαυτῷ</char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ Ψ 5 (81) 1243 1611 1739 1881<char style="add">c</char> 2492 <char style="it">Byz</char><char style="add">pt</char> <char style="it">l</char> 422 (<char style="it">l</char> 591) (<char style="it">l</char> 1153) <char style="it">l</char> 1159 <char style="it">l</char> 1441 <char style="it">l</char><char style="add">AD</char> arm eth (geo) Cyril; Augustine Speculum GNB NIV NRSV REB EU LB NBS TOB BTI DHH ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εν αυτω </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">without accents</char> A B* P ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 884</char></note>, ὁ μὴ πιστεύων τῷ θεῷ<note caller="6" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.10 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῷ θεῷ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ B Ψ 307 442 1175 1243 1448 1611 1735 1739<char style="add">c</char> 1852 1881 2492 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> (<char style="it">l</char> 592 <char style="it">l</char> 1441 </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸν θεόν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">) it<char style="add">l, q</char> syr<char style="add">p, h<char style="add">txt</char></char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">pt</char></char> slav Cyril; Augustine Varimadum ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῷ υἱῷ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A 5 81 436 642 1739* 2344 it<char style="add">ar</char> vg syr<char style="add">h<char style="add">mg</char></char> (eth) (geo) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τῷ υἱῷ τοῦ θεοῦ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">pt</char></char> arm ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰς τὸν υἱὸν τοῦ θεοῦ</char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">l</char> 884</char></note> ψεύστην πεποίηκεν αὐτόν, ὅτι οὐ πεπίστευκεν εἰς τὴν μαρτυρίαν ἣν μεμαρτύρηκεν ὁ θεὸς περὶ τοῦ υἱοῦ αὐτοῦ. <verse number="11" style="v" />καὶ αὕτη ἐστὶν ἡ μαρτυρία, ὅτι ζωὴν αἰώνιον ἔδωκεν ἡμῖν ὁ θεός<char style="add">♦</char>, καὶ αὕτη ἡ ζωὴ ἐν τῷ υἱῷ αὐτοῦ ἐστιν. <verse number="12" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.12 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 3:36">Jn 3.36</ref></char></note>ὁ ἔχων τὸν υἱὸν ἔχει τὴν ζωήν· ὁ μὴ ἔχων τὸν υἱὸν τοῦ θεοῦ τὴν ζωὴν οὐκ ἔχει.</para>
  <para style="s">The Knowledge of Eternal Life</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">5.13 </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JHN 20:31">Jn 20.31</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Ταῦτα ἔγραψα ὑμῖν, ἵνα εἰδῆτε ὅτι ζωὴν ἔχετε αἰώνιον, τοῖς πιστεύουσιν εἰς τὸ ὄνομα τοῦ υἱοῦ τοῦ θεοῦ. <verse number="14" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.14 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="MAT 7:7">Mt 7.7</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 14:13">Jn 14.13</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 15:7">15.7</ref>, <ref loc="JHN 15:16">16</ref>; <ref loc="JHN 16:23">16.23</ref>; <ref loc="1JN 3:21-22">1 Jn 3.21‑22</ref></char></note>καὶ αὕτη ἐστὶν ἡ παρρησία ἣν ἔχομεν πρὸς αὐτόν, ὅτι ἐάν τι αἰτώμεθα κατὰ τὸ θέλημα αὐτοῦ ἀκούει ἡμῶν. <verse number="15" style="v" />καὶ ἐὰν οἴδαμεν ὅτι ἀκούει ἡμῶν ὃ ἐὰν αἰτώμεθα, οἴδαμεν ὅτι ἔχομεν τὰ αἰτήματα ἃ ᾐτήκαμεν ἀπ᾽ αὐτοῦ.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">5.16 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ἔστιν … θάνατον </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="MAT 12:31">Mt 12.31</ref>; <ref loc="HEB 6:4-6">He 6.4‑6</ref></char>
    </note>Ἐάν τις ἴδῃ τὸν ἀδελφὸν αὐτοῦ ἁμαρτάνοντα ἁμαρτίαν μὴ πρὸς θάνατον, αἰτήσει καὶ δώσει αὐτῷ ζωήν, τοῖς ἁμαρτάνουσιν μὴ πρὸς θάνατον. ἔστιν ἁμαρτία πρὸς θάνατον· οὐ περὶ ἐκείνης λέγω ἵνα ἐρωτήσῃ. <verse number="17" style="v" />πᾶσα ἀδικία ἁμαρτία ἐστίν, καὶ ἔστιν ἁμαρτία οὐ<note caller="7" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.17 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">οὐ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B Ψ 048<char style="add">vid</char> 5 81 307 436 642 1175 1448 1611 1735 1739 1881 2344 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> vg<char style="add">st</char> syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> geo slav Origen Ps-Asterius ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">μή </char><char style="ft" closed="false">442 Clement ⫽ <char style="it">omit</char> 33 1243 1852 2492 it<char style="add">ar, l, t</char> vg<char style="add">cl, ww</char> syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> arm Tertullian</char></note> πρὸς θάνατον.</para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="18" style="v" />
    <note caller="*" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">5.18 </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">πᾶς … ἁμαρτάνει </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="1JN 3:9">1 Jn 3.9</ref> </char>
      <char style="xq" closed="false">ὁ γεννηθεὶς … αὐτοῦ </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">
        <ref loc="JHN 17:15">Jn 17.15</ref>
      </char>
    </note>Οἴδαμεν ὅτι πᾶς ὁ γεγεννημένος ἐκ τοῦ θεοῦ οὐχ ἁμαρτάνει, ἀλλ᾽ ὁ γεννηθεὶς ἐκ<note caller="8" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.18 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ὁ γεννηθεὶς ἐκ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B Ψ 5 81 307 436 442 642 1175 1243 1448 1611 1735 1739 1881 2344 2492 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> arm eth geo slav (Origen) ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἐγεννήθη· ὁ δὲ γεννηθεὶς ἐκ </char><char style="ft" closed="false">33 ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἡ γέννησις</char><char style="ft" closed="false">1852 it<char style="add">ar, l, q, t</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> Chromatius Jerome Vigilius</char></note> τοῦ θεοῦ τηρεῖ ἑαυτὸν<note caller="9" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.18 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{C} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">ἑαυτόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A<char style="add">c</char> Ψ 5 33 81 307 436 442 642 1175 1243 1448 1611 1735 1739 1881 2344 2492 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> arm eth geo slav Origen ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αὐτόν</char><char style="ft" closed="false">B<char style="add">2</char> 1852 it<char style="add">ar, l, t</char> vg Chromatius Jerome Vigilius GNB NIV NRSV REB EU LB BJ NBS TOB BTI DHH ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">αυτον</char><char style="ft" closed="false"><char style="it">without accents</char> A* B*</char></note> καὶ ὁ πονηρὸς οὐχ ἅπτεται αὐτοῦ. <verse number="19" style="v" />οἴδαμεν ὅτι ἐκ τοῦ θεοῦ ἐσμεν καὶ ὁ κόσμος ὅλος ἐν τῷ πονηρῷ κεῖται. <verse number="20" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.20 </char><char style="xq" closed="false">γινώσκωμεν … αἰώνιος </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="JHN 17:3">Jn 17.3</ref></char></note>οἴδαμεν δὲ ὅτι ὁ υἱὸς τοῦ θεοῦ ἥκει καὶ δέδωκεν ἡμῖν διάνοιαν, ἵνα γινώσκωμεν τὸν ἀληθινόν<note caller="10" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.20 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸν ἀληθινόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ<char style="add">2</char> B 81 307 442 1175 1243 1448 2492 <char style="it">Byz</char> [K L P] <char style="it">Lect</char> syr<char style="add">p</char> cop<char style="add">bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> arm Cyril<char style="add">1/4</char>; Hilary Faustinus Jerome Speculum Fulgentius<char style="add">3/4</char> ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸ ἀληθινόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ* it<char style="add">l, q</char> cop<char style="add">sa, bo<char style="add">mss</char></char> Varimadum Quodvultdeus ⫽ </char><char style="fk" closed="false">τὸν ἀληθινὸν θεόν </char><char style="ft" closed="false">A Ψ 5 33 436 642 1611 1735 1739 1852 1881 2344 <char style="it">l</char> 598 <char style="it">l</char> 884 <char style="it">l</char> 1590 it<char style="add">ar, (t)</char> vg syr<char style="add">h</char> cop<char style="add">bo</char> eth geo slav Athanasius Marcellus Didymus<char style="add">dub</char> Cyril<char style="add">3/4</char>; Augustine Fulgentius<char style="add">1/4</char> REB ⫽ <char style="it">potestatem</char> Ambrose</char></note>, καὶ ἐσμὲν ἐν τῷ ἀληθινῷ, ἐν τῷ υἱῷ αὐτοῦ Ἰησοῦ Χριστῷ. οὗτός ἐστιν ὁ ἀληθινὸς θεὸς καὶ ζωὴ αἰώνιος. <verse number="21" style="v" /><note caller="*" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">5.21 </char><char style="xt" closed="false"><ref loc="1CO 10:14">1 Cor 10.14</ref></char></note>Τεκνία, φυλάξατε ἑαυτὰ<char style="add">♦</char> ἀπὸ τῶν εἰδώλων.<note caller="11" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.21 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">{A} </char><char style="fk" closed="false">εἰδώλων. </char><char style="ft" closed="false">ℵ A B Ψ 5 33 436 442 642 1243 1448 1611 1735 1739 1881 2344 2492 <char style="it">l</char> 593 <char style="it">l</char> 5